A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22The%20MC%20130J%20Commando%20aircraft%20rolls%20onto%20the%20flight%20line%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F661701fe16bde8d4ead7a3eb%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22667%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%20MC%20130J%20Commando%20aircraft%20rolls%20onto%20the%20flight%20line%20during%20an%20arrival%20ceremony%20in%20Middletown%2C%20Pennsylvania.%3Cp%3EUS%20Air%20National%20Guard%20photo%20by%20Senior%20Airman%20Diana%20Snyder%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EThe%20MC-130J%20Commando%20II%20is%20an%20upgraded%20version%20of%20the%20C-130%20cargo%20plane.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EThe%20plane%20assists%20in%20infiltration%2C%20exfiltration%2C%20and%20resupply%20for%20special%20ops%20forces.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EThe%20US%20Air%20Force%20recently%20began%20utilizing%20the%20cargo%20plane%20to%20airdrop%20palletized%20munitions.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fc-130j-30-air-force-slideshow-2019-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EC-130%20cargo%20plane%3C%2Fa%3E%20was%20first%20designed%20in%201951.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMore%20than%20seven%20decades%20later%2C%20one%20of%20the%20plane's%20latest%20models%2C%20the%20MC-130J%2C%20is%20being%20fitted%20with%20a%20new%20weapons%20system%20that%20is%20changing%20how%20the%20US%20Air%20Force%20utilizes%20its%20fleet%20of%20existing%20planes.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3EThe%20first%20of%20its%20kind%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%224001%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22a%20%20large%20plane%20flying%20over%20the%20mountains%20in%20California%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6617027216bde8d4ead7a558%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223215%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%20first%20C-130%20Transport%20flying%20back%20from%20its%20early%20flight%20paces%20over%20California's%20Mojave%20Desert.%3Cp%3EBettmann%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20C-130%20Hercules%20was%20created%20to%20address%20deficiencies%20in%20the%20US%20Air%20Force%20fleet%20during%20the%20Korean%20War.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20US%20military%20recognized%20a%20need%20for%20a%20plane%20that%20could%20take%20off%20from%20shorter%20runways%20and%20transport%20more%20soldiers%20and%20supplies%20on%20and%20off%20the%20battlefield.%20At%20the%20time%2C%20no%20plane%20could%20simultaneously%20achieve%20all%20the%20objectives%20the%20Air%20Force%20needed.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Air%20Force%20asked%20for%20designs%20for%20a%20plane%20capable%20of%20hauling%20large%2C%20bulky%20equipment%20over%20long%20distances%2C%20landing%20in%20tight%20spaces%2C%20slowing%20to%20125%20knots%20for%20paratroop%20drops%2C%20and%20flying%20with%20one%20engine%20if%20needed.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBoeing%2C%20Douglas%2C%20and%20Fairchild%20submitted%20models%20for%20this%20new%20type%20of%20plane%2C%20but%20Lockheed's%20submission%20ultimately%20won%20the%20bid%20in%201951.%20To%20this%20day%2C%20Lockheed%20still%20makes%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fc-130-cargo-plane-2016%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EC-130%20models%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20their%20upgraded%20versions.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20a%202017%20interview%20with%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.popularmechanics.com%2Fmilitary%2Faviation%2Fa26156%2Fc-130-badass-plane%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EPopular%20Mechanics%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20Lockheed%20Martin%20historian%20Jeff%20Rhodes%20said%20the%20design%20team%20took%20the%20largest%20piece%20of%20equipment%20the%20Army%20needed%20to%20transport%2C%20%26quot%3Bdrew%20a%20circle%20around%20it%2C%20and%20that%20set%20the%20diameter%20of%20the%20fuselage.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20basic%20C-130%2C%20aft%20of%20the%20cockpit%20and%20before%20the%20ramp%2C%20is%20the%20length%20of%20a%20railroad%20boxcar%2C%26quot%3B%20Rhodes%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThree%20years%20later%2C%20the%20YC-130%2C%20a%20prototype%20of%20the%20later%20C-130%2C%20made%20its%20first%20test%20flight%20from%20Burbank%2C%20California%2C%20to%20Edwards%20Air%20Force%20Base%20in%20Kern%20County%2C%20California.%20It%20took%20off%20after%20using%20only%20855%20feet%20of%20runway%2C%20a%20fraction%20of%20the%205%2C000-foot%20ground%20roll%20needed%20by%20most%20other%20planes%20its%20size.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20US%20Air%20Force%20has%20not%20stopped%20production%20of%20the%20C-130%20class%20plane%20since%20it%20was%20invented%20in%20the%201950s%2C%20making%20it%20the%20longest%20continuous%20aircraft%20production%20run%20in%20history.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3E%E2%80%98The%20C-130%20is%20whatever%20is%20needed%E2%80%99%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20man%20stands%20on%20a%20platform%20with%20his%20hand%20on%20a%20truck%20being%20loaded%20into%20the%20back%20of%20a%20plane%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6617034b3f923f7dab069a45%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221363%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EA%20soldier%20loads%20M-998%20multipurpose%20wheeled%20vehicles%20into%20a%20C-130E%20Hercules%20aircraft.%3Cp%3EUSAF%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.lockheedmartin.com%2Fen-us%2Fnews%2Ffeatures%2Fhistory%2Fhercules.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ELockheed%20Martin%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20the%20C-130%20could%20originally%20carry%2040%2C000%20pounds%20of%20cargo%20and%20fly%20at%20360%20mph.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20years%20since%20its%20creation%2C%20the%20performance%20and%20usage%20of%20the%20C-130%20have%20exceeded%20expectations%2C%20and%20it%20has%20become%20known%20as%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmc130-transport-plane-has-support-special-ops-mission-since-vietnam-2021-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%26quot%3Bdo-it-all%26quot%3B%20plane%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20C-130%20is%20whatever%20is%20needed%2C%26quot%3B%20Rhodes%20told%20Popular%20Mechanics.%20%26quot%3BIt's%20an%20ambulance%2C%20it's%20a%20gunship%2C%20it%20drops%20paratroopers%2C%20it%20carries%20cargo%2C%20it's%20a%20TV%20broadcast%20system%2C%20it's%20launched%20drones%2C%20and%20caught%20satellites.%20You%20name%20it%2C%20the%20Hercules%20has%20done%20it%20at%20some%20point%20in%20its%20career.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%202010%20alone%2C%20the%20C-130%20series%20plane%20hauled%20more%20than%2013%2C600%20short%20tons%20of%20cargo%2C%20transported%20more%20than%2025%2C800%20passengers%2C%20and%20routed%20280%20patients%20from%20Haiti%20for%20medical%20evaluations%20after%20the%20country's%20devastating%20earthquake%2C%20according%20to%20Lockheed%20Martin.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3EFirst%20of%20many%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%225078%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20black-and-white%20photo%20of%20a%20large%20cargo%20plane%20with%20two%20propellers%20on%20each%20side%20inside%20a%20large%20warehouse%20full%20of%20planes%20of%20similar%20sizes.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F661703951caec1275a6eda42%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223650%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EA%20view%20of%20the%20first%20production%20version%20of%20the%20US%20Air%20Force's%20Lockheed%20C-130A%20Hercules%20military%20transports.%3Cp%3ELockheed%20Aircraft%20Company%2FPhotoQuest%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20C-130's%20high%20utility%20and%20versatility%20have%20contributed%20to%20its%20historic%20production%20run%20for%20the%20US%20Air%20Force.%20Since%20its%20creation%2C%20the%20plane%20has%20been%20in%20production%20for%20over%2070%20years.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20has%20roughly%2070%20variants%2C%20over%202%2C400%20aircraft%20have%20been%20produced%2C%20and%20it%20is%20used%20by%2070%20countries%20worldwide.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3EDurability%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221448%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20large%2C%20camouflaged%20C-130%20flying%20in%20the%20Antarctic%20with%20a%20snowy%20mountain%20in%20the%20background.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F661703ca16bde8d4ead7a5f0%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22896%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EA%20New%20Zealand%20Air%20Force%20C130%20Hercules%20lands%20on%20the%20ice%20runway%20at%20Scott%20Base%2C%20an%20Antarctic%20New%20Zealand%20research%20station.%3Cp%3EMicheal%20Field%2FAFP%20via%20Getty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20addition%20to%20its%20versatility%20and%20numerous%20variants%2C%20the%20C-130%20is%20also%20known%20for%20its%20durability.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEarly%20models%20of%20the%20C-130%20had%20four%20different%20engines%20delivering%203%2C750%20horsepower%20each.%20Newer%20models%2C%20like%20the%20MC-130J%2C%20have%20four%20Rolls-Royce%20AE%202100D3%20Turboprop%20engines.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20Wayne%20Roberts%2C%20Lockheed's%20chief%20experimental%20test%20pilot%2C%20the%20C-130%20and%20its%20variants%20are%20so%20versatile%20that%20they%20can%20stay%20in%20flight%20at%20speeds%20as%20low%20as%2080%20knots%20with%20only%20one%20engine%20working.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELockheed%20attributes%20the%20durability%20of%20the%20aircraft%20to%20using%20the%20four%20turboprop%20engines%2C%20which%20provide%20surplus%20power%20to%20the%20plane%20and%20pressurize%20the%20fuselage%2C%20including%20the%20cargo%20compartment.%20This%20allows%20the%20aircraft%20to%20fly%20efficiently%20at%20high%20altitudes.%20Lockheed%20strengthened%20the%20airframe%20to%20accommodate%20the%20added%20pressurization.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%201971%2C%20a%20C-130%2C%20call%20sign%20Juliet%20Delta%20321%2C%20crashed%20during%20a%20resupply%20mission%20in%20Antarctica%20after%20the%20rockets%20used%20in%20takeoff%20assistance%20malfunctioned.%20There%20were%20no%20casualties%2C%20but%20the%20C-130%20was%20left%20in%20the%20harsh