%26quot%3BSome%20members%20of%20Congress%20are%20in%20their%2070s%20and%2080s.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENot%20even%20members%20of%20the%20progressive%20%26quot%3BSquad%26quot%3B%20are%20on%20board%20with%20the%20idea.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI'm%20not%20in%20favor%20of%20telling%20people%20when%20they%20should%20retire%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Democratic%20Rep.%20Ilhan%20Omar%20of%20Minnesota.%20%26quot%3BI%20just%20think%20it's%20a%20waste%20of%20energy%20and%20time%20to%20have%20these%20silly%20debates.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20haven't%20really%20delved%20into%20that%20conversation%20much%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Rep.%20Alexandria%20Ocasio-Cortez%20of%20New%20York.%20%26quot%3BSo%20I%20don't%20really%20have%20much%20of%20a%20comment%20on%20it%20at%20the%20moment.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGenerally%2C%20those%20who%20want%20Sotomayor%20to%20step%20down%20have%20argued%20that%20the%2069-year-old%20justice's%20health%20could%20falter%20in%20the%20coming%20years%2C%20owing%20to%20her%20type%201%20diabetes%20diagnosis%20and%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.huffpost.com%2Fentry%2Fsonia-sotomayor-medic-retirement_n_65d8ec05e4b0cc1f2f7bab77%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EHuffington%20Post%3C%2Fa%3E%20report%20that%20she%20has%20traveled%20with%20a%20medic.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGiven%20the%20possibility%20of%20former%20President%20Donald%20Trump%20winning%20in%20November%20%E2%80%94%20or%20of%20Republicans%20retaking%20the%20Senate%20and%20refusing%20to%20confirm%20another%20Democratic%20nominee%20%E2%80%94%20the%20%26quot%3BRetire%20Sotomayor%26quot%3B%20crowd%20is%20aiming%20to%20safeguard%20against%20the%20possibility%20of%207-2%20conservative%20court.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHanging%20over%20the%20discussion%20is%20the%20late%20Associate%20Justice%20Ruth%20Bader%20Ginsburg%2C%20who%20died%20in%202020%20just%20months%20before%20the%20end%20of%20the%20Trump%20administration.%20Years%20earlier%2C%20Ginsburg%20had%20resisted%20calls%20to%20retire%20during%20the%20Obama%20administration.%20She%20was%20swiftly%20replaced%20by%20conservative%20Associate%20Justice%20Amy%20Coney%20Barrett%2C%20which%20laid%20the%20groundwork%20for%20decisions%20like%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsupreme-court-abortion-decision-final-ruling-scotus-roe-v-wade-2022-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eoverturning%20of%20Roe%20v.%20Wade%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20June%202022.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EYet%20there's%20little%20indication%20that%20Sotomayor%20isn't%20healthy%20enough%20to%20serve%2C%20and%20the%20arguments%20in%20favor%20of%20her%20retirement%20are%20built%20on%20a%20fair%20degree%20of%20speculation%20about%20her%20condition.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20now%2C%20calls%20for%20Sotomayor's%20retirement%20remain%20limited%20to%20some%20prominent%20progressives%20and%20media%20figures.%20Democratic%20Sen.%20Richard%20Blumenthal%20has%20gone%20the%20furthest%20of%20anyone%2C%20telling%20NBC%20News%20recently%20that%20Sotomayor%20%26quot%3Bhas%20to%20weigh%20the%20competing%20factors%26quot%3B%20and%20that%20Democrats%20%26quot%3Bshould%20learn%20a%20lesson%26quot%3B%20from%20Ginsburg.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20recent%20days%2C%20several%20other%20Democratic%20senators%20have%20told%20reporters%20that%20they%20oppose%20calls%20for%20the%20justice%20to%20retire.%20But%20while%20it's%20the%20Senate%20that%20deals%20with%20the%20confirmation%20of%20justices%2C%20the%20lower%20chamber%20also%20has%20some%20say%20over%20the%20court%2C%20too%3A%20the%20House%20could%20theoretically%20move%20to%20impeach%20a%20justice%2C%20if%20it%20came%20to%20that.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BTaking%20into%20account%20what%20happened%20to%20Ruth%20Bader%20Ginsburg%2C%20I%20get%20it%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Rep.%20Jimmy%20Gomez%20of%20California.%20But%20the%20progressive%20Democrat%20said%20that%20people%20need%20to%20%26quot%3Bchill%20out%26quot%3B%20about%20Sotomayor%2C%20noting%20that%20he%20was%20recently%20at%20an%20event%20with%20the%2094-year-old%20civil%20rights%20activist%20Dolores%20Huerta%2C%20and%20that%20she%20seemed%20healthy.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIronically%2C%20Gomez%20also%20pointed%20to%20Ginsburg%20%E2%80%94%20who%20survived%20several%20bouts%20of%20cancer%20and%20died%20at%20age%2087%20%E2%80%94%20to%20support%20his%20defense%20of%20Sotomayor.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI'm%20not%20concerned%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Gomez.%20%26quot%3BHow%20many%20health%20issues%20did%20Ruth%20Bader%20Ginsburg%20have%3F%20And%20she%20kept%20on%20trucking%20for%20years.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20think%20it's%20an%20overreaction%20to%20a%20recent%20experience%20on%20the%20court%20with%20Justice%20Ginsburg%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Rep.%20Chuy%20Garcia%2C%20a%20progressive%20Democrat%20from%20Illinois%2C%20saying%20that%20Sotomayor%20is%20an%20%26quot%3Bextraordinary%20Justice%26quot%3B%20whose%20%26quot%3Blived%20experience%20is%20very%20insightful%20to%20the%20court.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERep.%20Dean%20Phillips%20of%20Minnesota%20%E2%80%94%20who%20waged%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdean-phillips-campaign-president-biden-house-democrats-2024-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ean%20entire%20Democratic%20presidential%20primary%20campaign%3C%2Fa%3E%20based%20on%20the%20premise%20that%20Joe%20Biden%20is%20too%20old%20%E2%80%94%20said%20Sotomayor's%20situation%20is%20a%20%26quot%3Bvery%20different%20context%26quot%3B%20than%20Biden's.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20Phillips%20said%20that%20if%20it%20became%20clear%20that%20Sotomayor%20was%20gravely%20ill%2C%20he%20would%20have%20a%20different%20opinion.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThen%20it%20becomes%20an%20issue%20of%20great%20acute%20consequence%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Phillips.%20%26quot%3BRuth%20Bader%20Ginsburg%20was%20ill.%20We%20knew%20she%20had%20cancer.%20We%20knew%20she%20was%20old.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsonia-sotomay