22Russian%20President%20Vladimir%20Putin.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6618476016bde8d4ead821bf%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223249%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ERussia's%20state-sponsored%20mercenaries%20are%20expanding%20efforts%20to%20destabilize%20Africa%20and%20the%20Middle%20East.%3Cp%3EAlexander%20Zemlianichenko%2FAP%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3ETo%20Russia%2C%20the%20Ukraine%20war%20and%20the%20%26quot%3Bgray%20zone%26quot%3B%C2%A0%20fights%20beyond%20it%20are%20two%20sides%20of%20the%20same%20coin.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EDestabilizing%20Africa%20would%20ease%20Russia's%20campaign%20in%20Ukraine%2C%20the%20Kremlin%20believes.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EThe%20KGB's%20successors%2C%20however%2C%20have%20had%20a%20less%20than%20stellar%20record.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EEven%20as%20Russian%20bombs%20pound%20Ukraine%2C%20Moscow's%20mercenaries%20and%20spies%20are%20busy%20trying%20to%20set%20much%20of%20the%20rest%20of%20the%20world%20afire.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BRussia%20is%20using%20unconventional%20methods%20to%20expand%20its%20influence%2C%20evade%20containment%2C%20and%20destabilize%20and%20disrupt%20its%20adversaries%20%E2%80%94%20and%20is%20making%20progress%20in%20several%20directions%2C%26quot%3B%20warned%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.rusi.org%2Fexplore-our-research%2Fpublications%2Fspecial-resources%2Fthreat-russias-unconventional-warfare-beyond-ukraine-2022-24%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ereport%3C%2Fa%3E%20by%20Britain's%20Royal%20United%20Services%20Institute%20think%20tank.%20This%20includes%20covert%20operations%20in%20Europe%2C%20mercenaries%20operating%20across%20Africa%2C%20and%20establishing%20links%20with%20Muslim%20communities%20in%20Central%20Asia%20and%20Europe.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETo%20Russia%2C%20the%20conventional%20warfare%20waged%20in%20Ukraine%2C%20and%20unconventional%20%26quot%3Bgray%20zone%26quot%3B%20warfare%20waged%20around%20the%20world%2C%20are%20two%20sides%20of%20the%20same%20coin.%20%26quot%3BIt%20is%20the%20conventional%20threat%20of%20escalation%20that%20deters%20retaliation%20against%20unconventional%20activity%2C%20thereby%20expanding%20the%20scope%20of%20what%20Russia%20can%20get%20away%20with%2C%26quot%3B%20RUSI%20said.%20%26quot%3BConversely%2C%20it%20is%20the%20unconventional%20operations%20of%20the%20Russian%20special%20services%20that%20aim%20to%20set%20the%20conditions%20for%20the%20successful%20application%20of%20conventional%20military%20force.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThus%2C%20for%20example%2C%20destabilizing%20Africa%20%E2%80%94%20and%20diverting%20Western%20attention%20and%20resources%20%E2%80%94%20will%20ease%20Russia's%20campaign%20in%20Ukraine%2C%20the%20Kremlin%20believes.%20All%20of%20this%20means%20that%20Russian%20%26quot%3Bspecial%20services%26quot%3B%20%E2%80%94%20spies%2C%20assassins%2C%20and%20propagandists%20%E2%80%94%20will%20continue%20their%20efforts.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERevolution%20and%20subversion%20was%20the%20business%20model%20for%20the%20Soviet%20Union%20and%20later%20Russia.%20%26quot%3BThe%20Russian%20playbook%20has%20been%20remarkably%20consistent%20for%20decades%2C%26quot%3B%20noted%20RUSI.%20%26quot%3BThe%20overall%20approach%20is%20to%20use%20information%20operations%20and%20active%20measures%20to%20polarize%20a%20target%20population%2C%20mobilize%20factions%20in%20support%20of%20allied%20elites%2C%20and%20paralyze%20support%20for%20opposing%20elements%20of%20a%20country's%20leadership.%20Human%20intelligence%20operations%20are%20used%20to%20attempt%20elite%20capture%20through%20the%20offer%20of%20assistance%20to%20politicians%20who%20support%20Russian%20interests.%20Finally%2C%20violence%20can%20be%20employed%20to%20escalate%20political%20tensions%20to%20the%20point%20of%20crisis%2C%20or%20in%20other%20contexts%20to%20isolate%20a%20captured%20elite.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20example%2C%20in%202016%2C%20Russian%20military%20intelligence%20recruited%20criminal%20gangs%20for%20an%20attempted%20coup%20to%20stop%20Montenegro%20from%20joining%20NATO%20(the%20attempt%20eventually%20led%20to%20several%20agents%20and%20Montenegrin%20politicians%20being%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.theguardian.com%2Fworld%2F2019%2Fmay%2F09%2Fmontenegro-convicts-pro-russia-politicians-of-coup-plot%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ejailed%3C%2Fa%3E).%20In%20February%202022%2C%20Moscow%20tried%20to%20spark%20street%20protests%20that%20would%20%26quot%3Bjustify%20Russian%20military%20intervention%2C%20aided%20by%20collaborators%20within%20the%20Ukrainian%20government%2C%20clearing%20the%20path%20for%20Russian%20agents%20recruited%20inside%20the%20Ukrainian%20parliament%20and%20state%20to%20seize%20power%2C%26quot%3B%20RUSI%20said.%20And%20in%20Moldova%20in%202022%20and%202023%2C%20Russia's%20FSB%20security%20service%20hoped%20that%20protests%20would%20offer%20an%20excuse%20for%20pro-Russian%20leaders%20to%20call%20for%20military%20intervention%20(though%20%26quot%3Bthe%20poor%20performance%20of%20Russian%20arms%20in%20Ukraine%26quot%3B%20made%20these%20leaders%20hesitate%2C%20RUSI%20noted).%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22An%20aerial%20view%20of%20the%20Main%20Directorate%20of%20the%20General%20Staff%20of%20the%20Armed%20Forces%20building%2C%20also%20known%20as%20the%20GRU%2C%20in%20Moscow%2C%20Russia.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F66182dc51caec1275a6f3f28%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22981%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EAn%20aerial%20view%20of%20the%20Main%20Directorate%20of%20the%20General%20Staff%20of%20the%20Armed%20Forces%20building%2C%20also%20known%20as%20the%20GRU%2C%20in%20Moscow%2C%20Russia.%3Cp%3EGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Ch2%3E'Creating%20crises'%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EUnfortunately%20for%20Russian%20President%20Vladimir%20Putin%2C%20the%20KGB's%20successors%20have%20had%20a%20less-than-stellar%20record.%20The%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nytimes.com%2F2019%2F10%2F08%2Fworld%2Feurope%2Funit-29155-russia-gru.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E161%20Intelligence%20Specialists%20Training%20Center%3C%2Fa%3E%20%E2%80%94%20the%20shadowy%20sabotage%2C%20subversion%2C%20and%20assassination%20unit%20of%20the%20GRU%2C%20or%20Russian%20military%20intelligence%20%E2%80%94%20has%20accrued%20multiple%20failures%20over%20the%20last%20decade%2C%20including%20an%20unsuccessful%20coup%20in%20Montenegro%20in%202016%2C%20and%20attempts%20to%20foment%20violence%20in%20Ukraine%20and%20Moldova%20to%20justify%20Russian%20military%20intervention.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20reasons%20for%20failure%20were%20consistent%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20RUSI%20analysts%20Jack%20Watling%2C%20Oleksandr%20Danylyuk%20and%20Nick%20Reynolds.%20%26quot%3BPoor%20operational%20security%20leading%20to%20the%20exposure%20of%20the%20plan%20to%20domestic%20security%20services%20and%20the%20disruption%20of%20its%20implementation%3B%20and%20inaccurate%20assessment%20by%20the%20Russian%20special%20services%20as%20to%20the%20extent%20of%20their%20influence%20in%20these%20countries.%26quot%3B%20In%20addition%2C%20many%20European%20nations%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.csis.org%2Fanalysis%2Fcurtailing-russia-diplomatic-expulsions-and-war-ukraine%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eexpelled%3C%2Fa%3E%20Russian%20diplomats%20and%20spies%20after%20the%20February%202022%20invasion%20of%20Ukraine.%20Inept%20operations%20%E2%80%94%20such%20as%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.theguardian.com%2Fworld%2F2020%2Fjun%2F23%2Fskripal-salisbury-poisoning-decline-of-russia-spy-agencies-gru%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ebotched%20assassinations%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%20GRU%20defectors%20in%20Britain%20%E2%80%94%20also%20didn't%20help.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EUndaunted%2C%20Russia%20has%20rebuilt%20its%20capacity%20for%20unconventional%20warfare%20capabilities%2C%20or%20%26quot%3Bactive%20measures.%26quot%3B%20To%20create%20a%20support%20network%20for%20its%20agents%20in%20Europe%2C%20it%20has%20switched%20from%20using%20Russian%20businessmen%20and%20expatriates%20to%20utilizing%20the%20Russian%20mafia%20and%20recruiting%20foreign%20students%20at%20Russian%20universities.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAs%20the%20war%20in%20Ukraine%20protracts%2C%20Russia%20has%20an%20interest%20in%20creating%20crises%20further%20afield%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20RUSI.%20%26quot%3BThe%20Balkans%20present%20a%20particularly%20serious%20set%20of%20opportunities%20for%20such%20enterprises.%20Russia%20also%20has%20an%20active%20interest%20in%20destabilizing%20Ukraine's%20partners%2C%20and%20with%20a%20slew%20of%20elections%20forthcoming%20across%20Europe%20there%20is%20a%20wide%20range%20of%20opportunities%20to%20exacerbate%20polarization.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMeanwhile%2C%20Russia's%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bbc.com%2Fnews%2Fworld-africa-68322230%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Estate-sponsored%20mercenaries%3C%2Fa%3E%20are%20expanding%20their%20efforts%20in%20Africa%20and%20the%20Middle%20East%20by%20providing%20military%20support%20to%20dictators%20and%20warlords%2C%20from%20Libya%20and%20Mali%20to%20Sudan%20and%20the%20Central%20African%20Republic.%20The%20infamous%20Wagner%20Group%20%E2%80%94%20a%20private%20military%20corporation%20%E2%80%94%20seems%20to%20be%20subsumed%2C%20its%20leader%20Yevgeny%20Prigozhin%20having%20opposed%20Putin%20before%20dying%20in%20a%20mysterious%20plane%20crash.%20Instead%2C%20Russia%20is%20now%20offering%20a%20%26quot%3Bregime%20survival%20package%26quot%3B%20%E2%80%94%20delivered%20via%20a%20GRU%20Expeditionary%20Corps%20of%20mercenary%20groups%20such%20as%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.france24.com%2Fen%2Feurope%2F20230408-new-russian-militia-convoy-rises-as-wagner-group-gets-too-big-to-control%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EConvoy%3C%2Fa%3E%20%E2%80%94%20to%20support%20clients%20against%20threats%20from%20Islamic%20rebel