0how%20corporate%20ownership%20affects%20medical%20care%2C%20especially%20when%20it's%20a%20giant%20like%20UnitedHealth%20or%20CVS%20doing%20the%20buying.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESome%20doctors%20and%20experts%20in%20the%20industry%20fear%20corporate%20owners%20could%20prioritize%20their%20investors%20and%20profits%20ahead%20of%20patients%2C%20and%20doctors%20could%20lose%20the%20ability%20to%20make%20their%20own%20decisions%20about%20what's%20best%20for%20a%20patient.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20big%20guys%20aren't%20cheaper.%20They%20don't%20deliver%20better%20customer%20service%2C%20they%20aren't%20more%20timely%2C%20none%20of%20that.%20They're%20just%20able%20to%20negotiate%20higher%20prices%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Farzad%20Mostashari%2C%20the%20CEO%20of%20Aledade%2C%20a%20company%20that%20aims%20to%20help%20primary%20care%20practices%20stay%20independent.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20federal%20government%20is%20starting%20to%20pay%20attention.%20In%20March%2C%20it%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ftc.gov%2Fnews-events%2Fnews%2Fpress-releases%2F2024%2F03%2Ffederal-trade-commission-department-justice-department-health-human-services-launch-cross-government%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Elaunched%3C%2Fa%3E%20an%20inquiry%20into%20PE%20firms%20and%20other%20corporate%20owners'%20%26quot%3Bincreasing%20control%20over%20healthcare%26quot%3B%20and%20how%20this%20might%20threaten%20patients'%20access%20to%20affordable%20and%20quality%20care.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20feds%20also%20zeroed%20in%20on%20UnitedHealth%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.wsj.com%2Fhealth%2Fhealthcare%2Fu-s-launches-antitrust-investigation-of-healthcare-giant-unitedhealth-ff5a00d2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ereportedly%3C%2Fa%3E%20facing%20an%20antitrust%20investigation%20by%20the%20US%20Justice%20Department%20into%20how%20its%20medical%20group%20acquisitions%20affect%20consumers%20and%20competitors.%20News%20of%20the%20probe%20surfaced%20before%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fchange-healthcare-cyberattack-small-mental-health-practices-payments-money-2024-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ecyberattack%20on%20UnitedHealth's%3C%2Fa%3E%20technology%20business%2C%20Change%20Healthcare%2C%20caused%20hospitals%20and%20clinics%20nationwide%20to%20forgo%20billions%20in%20payments%20%E2%80%94%20raising%20more%20questions%20about%20UnitedHealth's%20chokehold%20on%20the%20healthcare%20industry.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EDoctors%20are%20hot%20commodities%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20tough%20to%20lump%20the%20many%20buyers%20of%20medical%20practices%20together%2C%20as%20they're%20pursuing%20different%20strategies.%20But%2C%20in%20essence%2C%20they're%20all%20hiring%20doctors%20for%20their%20relationships%20with%20patients%2C%20who%20bring%20opportunities%20for%20more%20profits.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgen-z-millennials-giving-up-medical-care-cant-afford-costs-2024-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EUS%20healthcare%20spending%3C%2Fa%3E%20reached%20%244.5%20trillion%20in%202022%2C%20representing%20almost%20a%20fifth%20of%20the%20national%20GDP.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHospitals%20rely%20on%20doctors%20%E2%80%94%20especially%20those%20who%20provide%20primary%20care%20%E2%80%94%20to%20refer%20patients%20for%20lucrative%20procedures%20or%20surgeries.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Funitedhealth-stock-exec-medical-costs-rising-2023-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EInsurers%20like%20UnitedHealthcare%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20CVS'%20Aetna%20are%20required%20by%20federal%20law%20to%20spend%20most%20of%20the%20money%20they%20collect%20in%20premiums%20on%20medical%20care.%20Still%2C%20they%20can%20pocket%20more%20of%20those%20premiums%20by%20sending%20patients%20to%20clinics%20they%20own.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPharmacies%20hope%20that%20buying%20medical%20practices%20will%20give%20more%20prescriptions%20to%20fill%20and%20get%20more%20customers%20to%20buy%20over-the-counter%20products%20at%20the%20front%20of%20the%20store.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThey%20all%20realize%20that%20patients%20will%20follow%20what%20their%20doctors%20tell%20them%20to%20do%20or%20where%20their%20doctors%20tell%20them%20to%20go%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Chas%20Roades%2C%20a%20longtime%20healthcare%20consultant.%20%26quot%3BSo%20it%20allows%20them%20to%20both%20drive%20traffic%20to%20a%20downstream%20profit%20model%20that%20they're%20interested%20in%20growing%2C%20and%20I%20think%20it%20also%20is%20a%20way%20to%20get%20consumers%20to%20trust%20them.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMeanwhile%2C%20independent%20doctors%20have%20a%20tough%20time%20going%20it%20alone.%20Reimbursement%20is%20shrinking%2C%20and%20small%20practices%20don't%20have%20the%20ability%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ama-assn.org%2Fsystem%2Ffiles%2F2022-prp-practice-arrangement.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Enegotiate%20higher%20rates%3C%2Fa%3E%20as%20big%20hospital%20systems%20do.%20Plus%2C%20running%20a%20modern%20medical%20practice%20is%20expensive%2C%20requiring%20investments%20in%20staffing%2C%20technology%2C%20and%20electronic%20health%20records.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fai-chatbots-tech-doctors-medicine-healthcare-system-empathy-quality-email-2023-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EThe%20pandemic%3C%2Fa%3E%20made%20things%20even%20more%20challenging%2C%20spurring%20many%20doctors%20to%20sell%20their%20private%20practices.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20quiet%20takeover%20of%20physician%20practices%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EMuch%20of%20the%20takeover%20of%20physician%20practices%20has%20slid%20under%20the%20radar.%20That's%20because%20acquisitions%20valued%20below%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ftc.gov%2Fenforcement%2Fcompetition-matters%2F2024%2F02%2Fnew-hsr-thresholds-filing-fees-2024%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%24119.5%20million%3C%2Fa%3E%20don't%20have%20to%20be%20reported%20to%20federal%20regulators%2C%20and%20many%20practice%20purchases%20don't%20meet%20that%20threshold.%20Publicly%20traded%20UnitedHealth%2C%20for%20instance%2C%20rarely%20announces%20its%20purchases%20of%20medical%20groups%20and%20surgery%20centers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe're%20really%20flying%20blind%20here%20with%20respect%20to%20understanding%20how%20many%20acquisitions%20by%20which%20entities%20and%20what%20geographies%20and%20what%20specialties%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Yashaswini%20Singh%2C%20an%20assistant%20professor%20at%20Brown%20University%20who%20studies%20healthcare%20consolidation.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20lack%20of%20disclosure%20has%20made%20consolidating%20doctor%20practices%20difficult%20to%20study.%20Research%20into%20private%20equity's%20effects%20on%20healthcare%20is%20just%20emerging%2C%20and%20there's%20little%20to%20no%20academic%2C%20peer-reviewed%20research%20on%20how%20other%20corporate%20owners'%20acquisitions%20affect%20healthcare%20prices%20and%20quality%2C%20Singh%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EStudies%2C%20including%20Singh's%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fjamanetwork.com%2Fjournals%2Fjama-health-forum%2Ffullarticle%2F2795946%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eresearch%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20have%20shown%2C%20however%2C%20that%20PE%20ownership%20leads%20to%20steeper%20prices%20and%20more%20utilization%2C%20meaning%20patients%20may%20have%20more%20frequent%20doctor's%20appointments.%20Together%2C%20that%20drives%20healthcare%20costs%20higher.%20Research%20also%20suggests%20that%20PE%20ownership%20of%20nursing%20homes%20and%20hospitals%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fjamanetwork.com%2Fjournals%2Fjama%2Farticle-abstract%2F2813379%3FguestAccessKey%3De0cef9be-d55c-4bcf-8892-412af8f24355%26utm_source%3DFor_The_Media%26utm_medium%3Dreferral%26utm_campaign%3Dftm_links%26utm_content%3Dtfl%26utm_term%3D122623%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eworsens%20the%20quality%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%20care.%20One%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nber.org%2Fsystem%2Ffiles%2Fworking_papers%2Fw28474%2Fw28474.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Epaper%3C%2Fa%3E%20found%20that%20patients%20who%20went%20to%20nursing%20homes%20owned%20by%20private%20equity%20firms%20had%20a%2010%25%20greater%20chance%20of%20dying.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnd%20yet%2C%20private%20equity%20companies%20are%20rapidly%20expanding%20their%20presence%20in%20healthcare.%20A%202023%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.antitrustinstitute.org%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F07%2FAAI-UCB-EG_Private-Equity-I-Physician-Practice-Report_FINAL.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Estudy%3C%2Fa%3E%20found%20that%20one%20private%20equity%20firm%20owned%2030%25%20of%20the%20market%20share%20for%20physician%20practices%20in%20over%20a%20quarter%20of%20metropolitan%20areas%20across%20the%20US.%20A%20single%20PE%20firm%20owned%20over%20half%20the%20market%20share%20in%20some%20areas.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E'An%20unsatisfying%20way%20of%20practicing%20medicine'%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EAcquisitions%20by%20other%20corporate%20giants%20might%20not%20produce%20the%20same%20outcomes%20as%20PE%20firms%2C%20said%20Zirui%20Song%2C%20an%20associate%20professor%20of%20healthcare%20policy%20and%20medicine%20at%20Harvard%20Medical%20School%20who%20studies%20private%20equity%20in%20healthcare.%20PE%20firms%20are%20unique%20in%20holding%20on%20to%20their%20acquisitions%20for%20only%20a%20few%20years%20and%20saddling%20their%20acquired%20companies%20with%20debt%20and%20fees.%20Owners%20who%20hang%20on%20to%20their%20medical%20groups%20might%20be%20more%20motivated%20to%20improve%20services%2C%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnecdotally%2C%20though%2C%20many%20doctors%20don't%20like%20working%20for%20corporate%20overlords%2C%20Roades%20said.%20Older%20physicians%20who%20own%20equity%20in%20their%20medical%20practice%20get%20a%20nice%20payday%20when%20they%20sell%2C%20but%20the%20younger%20ones%20left%20behind%20are%20closely%20managed%20and%20measured%20in%20terms%20of%20cost%20and%20productivity%2C%20he%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20%26quot%3Ban%20unsatisfying%20way%20of%20practicing%20medicine.%20We're%20seeing%20a%20growing%20number%20of%20disgruntled%20early%20and%20mid-career%20physicians%20in%20these%20groups%20who%20find%20themselves%20suddenly%20working%20for%20large%20corporations%2C%20and%20this%20is%20not%20what%20they%20wanted%20to%20do%20with%20their%20lives%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%20a%20few%20years%20working%20at%20Optum-owned%20Oregon%20Medical%20Group%2C%20Dr.%20Nick%20Jones%20opened%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdirect-primary-care-a-no-insurance-healthcare-model-2017-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Edirect%20primary%20care%20practice%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20a%20type%20of%20clinic%20that%20charges%20a%20monthly%20fee%20instead%20of%20billing%20insurance.%20He%20said%20there's%20a%20sense%20of%20powerlessness%20for%20primary-care%20doctors%20in%20the%20traditional%20healthcare%20system%20%E2%80%94%20whether%20they're%20employed%20by%20Optum%2C%20a%20large%20hospital%20system%2C%20a%20private-equity%20firm%2C%20or%20a%20nonprofit%20clinic.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWith%20thousands%20of%20patients%20to%20treat%2C%20they%20face%20a%20mountain%20of%20administrative%20paperwork%20and%20have%20no%20control%20over%20their%20schedules.%20These%20problems%20stem%20from%20the%20fact%20that%20primary-care%20doctors%20are%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fkffhealthnews.org%2Fnews%2Farticle%2Fcompensation-pay-primary-care-shortage-solution%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eunderpaid%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20the%20traditional%20%26quot%3B%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.commonwealthfund.org%2Fpublications%2Fnewsletter-article%2Fmoving-health-care-system-away-fee-service%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Efee-for-service%3C%2Fa%3E%26quot%3B%20healthcare%20system%2C%20in%20which%20doctors%20are%20paid%20for%20every%20visit%2C%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20he%20felt%20supported%20at%20his%20previous%20Optum-owned%20clinic%20because%20of%20his%20office%20manager%2C%20%26quot%3Bthe%20financial%20underpinnings%20and%20the%20economics%20of%20medicine%26quot%3B%20made%20it%20unsustainable%20and%20stressful%2C%20Jones%20said.%20%26quot%3BThere%20was%20a%20three%20or%20four%20month%20wait%20for%20patients%20to%20see%20me.%20There%20was%20still%20too%20much%20on%20our%20plate%20to%20do%2C%20and%20%5Bduring%20the%20pandemic%5D%20there%20weren't%20enough%20medical%20assistants%20or%20case%20managers%20or%20nutritionists%20or%20other%20support%20to%20make%2020%20patients%20a%20day%20feel%20like%20the%20right%20thing%20to%20do.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EDoctors%20worry%20corporate%20giants%20put%20profits%20over%20patients%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20insurers%20and%20retailers%20say%20care%20is%20better%20and%20cheaper%20when%20integrated%20under%20one%20roof%2C%20connected%20to%20the%20health%20plan%2C%20pharmacy%2C%20or%20other%20provider%20organizations.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20its%20part%2C%20Optum%20says%20it%20wants%20to%20improve%20the%20health%20and%20well-being%20of%20people%20and%20lower%20the%20cost%20of%20care%20with%20integrated%20care%20teams%20and%20better%20technology.%20It%20says%20it's%20helping%20clinics%20transition%20to%20providing%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Foptumhealth-ceo-plans-to-make-clinics-a-100-billion-business-2021-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%26quot%3Bvalue-based%26quot%3B%3C%2Fa%3E%20or%20%26quot%3Baccountable%26quot%3B%20care%2C%20which%20means%20that%20its%20doctors%20get%20paid%20fixed%20fees%20upfront%20that%2C%20in%20theory%2C%20encourages%20them%20to%20keep%20patients%20healthy%20and%20order%20fewer%20unnecessary%20tests.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOptum%20said%20in%20a%20statement%20it%20continues%20%26quot%3Bto%20focus%20on%20supporting%20physicians%2C%20advance%20practice%20clinicians%2C%20and%20nurses%20in%20closing%20gaps%20in%20care%20and%20helping%20the%20health%20system%20perform%20better%20for%20everyone.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20spokesperson%20pointed%20to%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fjamanetwork.com%2Fjournals%2Fjamanetworkopen%2Ffullarticle%2F2799376%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Estudy%3C%2Fa%3E%20by%20Optum%20published%20in%20JAMA%20Network%20Open%20in%20December%202022%20that%20found%20seniors%20in%20value-based%20care%20arrangements%20were%20less%20likely%20than%20seniors%20in%20traditional%20payment%20models%20to%20visit%20the%20emergency%20room%2C%20or%20be%20admitted%20at%20the%20hospital%20for%20COPD%2C%20asthma%2C%20stroke%2C%20or%20heart%20attack.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20there%20are%20potential%20dangers.%20Patients%20may%20end%20up%20with%20fewer%20choices%20as%20bigger%20companies%20edge%20out%20competitors.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECalifornia%20health%20system%20Emanate%20Health%20sued%20Optum%20in%202023%20for%20anticompetitive%20behavior.%20It%20alleged%20that%20Optum%20canceled%20its%20contracts%20with%20Emanate%20hospitals%20and%20steered%20patients%20away%20after%20Emanate%20refused%20to%20agree%20to%20certain%20terms.%20Among%20the%20terms%3A%20Emanate%20primary-care%20doctors%20would%20serve%20only%20Optum%20patients%2C%20and%20Optum%20would%20get%20first%20dibs%20if%20Emanate%20decided%20to%20sell%20its%20primary-care%20practices.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECare%20might%20also%20feel%20less%20personal.%20Some%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fone-medical-patients-affected-unitedhealthcare-mount-sinai-dispute-2024-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EOne%20Medical%20patients%3C%2Fa%3E%20complained%20that%20since%20the%20chain%20folded%20into%20Amazon%2C%20their%20appointments%20were%20shortened%2C%20and%20certain%20features%20for%20seniors%2C%20like%20having%20health%20coaches%20available%20during%20patient%20visits%2C%20went%20away%2C%20according%20to%20a%20report%20from%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.washingtonpost.com%2Ftechnology%2F2024%2F02%2F28%2Famazon-health-one-medical%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EThe%20Washington%20Post%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EPatients%20could%20end%20up%20spending%20less%20time%20with%20doctors%20and%20face%20higher%20costs%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EDr.%20Mitch%20Li%2C%20an%20emergency%20physician%20who%20started%20Take%20Medicine%20Back%2C%20a%20group%20that%20opposes%20corporate%20owners%20pushing%20into%20healthcare%2C%20said%20patients%20will%20spend%20less%20time%20with%20their%20doctors%20and%20potentially%20face%20higher%20costs%20from%20predatory%20billing%20practices.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20corporate%20practice%20of%20medicine%20is%20the%20reason%20why%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgen-z-millennials-giving-up-medical-care-cant-afford-costs-2024-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ehealthcare%20costs%3C%2Fa%3E%20are%20out%20of%20control%2C%26quot%3B%20Li%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAbove%20all%2C%20some%20doctors%20fear%20having%20to%20make%20decisions%20that%20benefit%20the%20owner's%20bottom%20line%2C%20even%20though%20they%20may%20not%20be%20the%20best%20option%20for%20a%20patient.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDr.%20Michelle%20Cooke%2C%20a%20primary-care%20physician%2C%20previously%20practiced%20at%20an%20Atlanta%20clinic%20owned%20by%20a%20hospital%20system.%20Though%20the%20system%20was%20not-for-profit%2C%20it%20didn't%20operate%20like%20that%2C%20and%20over%20time%2C%20the%20job%20became%20unbearable%2C%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EShe%20had%20more%20than%203%2C000%20patients%20assigned%20to%20her%20care%20%E2%80%94%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.jabfm.org%2Fcontent%2Fjabfp%2F29%2F4%2F496.full.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Efar%20more%3C%2Fa%3E%20than%20typical%20%E2%80%94%20and%20appointments%20were%20too%20short%2C%20especially%20for%20the%20chronically%20ill%2C%20she%20said.%20The%20hospital%20system%20would%20prioritize%20lucrative%20physicals%20for%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcigna-selling-medicare-advantage-business-insurers-higher-costs-slower-growth-2024-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EMedicare%20patients%3C%2Fa%3E%20rather%20than%20seeing%20patients%20with%20an%20urgent%20need.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt%20really%20got%20to%20the%20point%20where%20I%20feel%20like%20I%20was%20working%20to%20feed%20the%20corporation%2C%26quot%3B%20Cooke%20said.%20%26quot%3BIt%20really%20wasn't%20incentivizing%20what%20the%20patients%20needed.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECooke%20has%20since%20opened%20a%20direct%20primary%20care%20practice%2C%20where%20she%20sees%20just%20a%20few%20hundred%20patients%20and%20can%20spend%20more%20time%20with%20them.%20She%20said%20she's%20found%20that%20she%20prescribes%20less%20medication%20now%20because%20she%20has%20time%20to%20educate%20patients%20on%20lifestyle%20habits%20and%20nutrition.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20federal%20government%20and%20states%20are%20dialing%20up%20the%20scrutiny%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Federal%20Trade%20Commission%2C%20the%20US%20Department%20of%20Justice%2C%20and%20the%20Department%20of%20Health%20and%20Human%20Services%20are%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.wsj.com%2Farticles%2Ffederal-agencies-probe-private-equity-profiteering-in-healthcare-2ba4c23a%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Estepping%20up%20scrutiny%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%20healthcare%20deals%2C%20particularly%20those%20backed%20by%20private-equity%20firms.%20The%20agencies%20also%20signaled%20that%20they%20want%20to%20look%20at%20smaller%20deals%20that%20typically%20wouldn't%20trigger%20an%20antitrust%20review.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESeveral%20states%20have%20also%20increased%20their%20oversight%20of%20local%20healthcare%20consolidation.%20Some%20state%20lawmakers%20are%20also%20trying%20to%20strengthen%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nejm.org%2Fdoi%2Ffull%2F10.1056%2FNEJMp2306904%23f1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Elaws%20prohibiting%3C%2Fa%3E%20corporations%20from%20practicing%20medicine.%20Most%20states%20have%20these%20bans%20on%20the%20books%2C%20but%20companies%20have%20found%20various%20ways%20around%20them.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20unclear%20if%20any%20of%20these%20efforts%20will%20meaningfully%20slow%20the%20corporatization%20of%20healthcare.%20And%2C%20to%20be%20sure%2C%20some%20physician%20practices%20may%20not%20have%20survived%20without%20an%20infusion%20of%20capital%20from%20a%20corporate%20buyer.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20bill%20introduced%20by%20Oregon%20State%20Rep.%20Ben%20Bowman%20would%20have%20closed%20certain%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.opb.org%2Farticle%2F2024%2F02%2F22%2Foregon-lawmakers-could-limit-corporate-ownership-of-medical-practices%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eloopholes%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20put%20more%20distance%20between%20corporate%20entities%20and%20their%20medical%20practices.%20Bowman%20told%20Business%20Insider%20he%20wanted%20to%20prevent%20big%20businesses%20from%20eroding%20doctors'%20autonomy.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BA%20physician%20who%20went%20to%20medical%20school%20who%20took%20an%20oath%20%E2%80%94%20their%20highest%20ethical%20duty%20is%20to%20care%20for%20their%20patients.%20Whether%20it's%20a%20private%20equity%20firm%20or%20a%20large%20corporation%2C%20their%20highest%20ethical%20duty%20is%20to%20generate%20a%20return%20on%20investment%20for%20their%20shareholders.%20Those%20two%20incentives%20are%20fundamentally%20at%20odds%2C%26quot%3B%20Bowman%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20bill%2C%20opposed%20by%20Amazon%20and%20CVS%2C%20died%20in%20March%2C%20but%20Bowman%20said%20he%20plans%20to%20reintroduce%20it%20in%202025.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAround%20the%20same%20time%20the%20bill%20died%2C%20UnitedHealth's%20Optum%20and%20The%20Corvallis%20Clinic%20%E2%80%94%20the%20small%20Oregon%20medical%20practice%20that%20Optum%20struck%20a%20deal%20to%20buy%20%E2%80%94%20requested%20that%20their%20tie-up%20receive%20an%20emergency%20exemption%20from%20state%20review%20because%20of%20the%20Oregon%20clinic's%20deteriorating%20finances.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20proposed%20acquisition%2C%20first%20announced%20in%20December%2C%20had%20received%20plenty%20of%20pushback%20from%20state%20residents.%20The%20request%20also%20came%20as%20hospitals%20and%20clinics%20nationwide%20faced%20cash%20shortfalls%20because%20of%20the%20cyberattack%20on%20UnitedHealth's%20Change%20Healthcare.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20week%20later%2C%20Oregon's%20health%20authority%20approved%20the%20request.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbig-corporations-unitedhealth-optum-cvs-walgreens-taking-over-healthcare-industry-2024-4%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1712864215000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F660dbaef1caec1275a6c9983%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbig-corporations-unitedhealth-optum-cvs-walgreens-taking-over-healthcare-industry-2024-4%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Corporate%20owners%2C%20from%20UnitedHealth%20to%20private-equity%20firms%2C%20are%20devouring%20physician%20practices%2C%20making%20independent%20doctors%20a%20relic%20of%20the%20past.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22slivingston%40businessinsider.com%20(Shelby%20Livingston)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A8%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbig-corporations-unitedhealth-optum-cvs-walgreens-taking-over-healthcare-industry-2024-4%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Taylor%20Swift's%20music%20returns%20to%20TikTok%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1712864126000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fichef.bbci.co.uk%2Fnews%2F1024%2Fbranded_news%2FC082%2Fproduction%2F_133128294_gettyimages-1978661546.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bbc.co.uk%2Fnews%2Fentertainment-arts-68794119%231%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20artist's%20songs%20were%20removed%20from%20the%20platform%20in%20January%20after%2