reported%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nytimes.com%2F1991%2F08%2F04%2Fus%2F17-killed-and-a-life-is-searched-for-clues.html%5C%22%3E%20The%20New%20York%20Times.%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20police%20responded%2C%20Jeffrey%20Dahmer%20told%20the%20officers%20the%20boy%20was%20his%20lover%20and%20that%20they%20had%20a%20flight.%20After%20the%20officers%20returned%20the%20boy%20to%20Dahmer%20and%20escorted%20them%20both%20home%2C%20Dahmer%20killed%20him.%20Dahmer%20went%20on%20to%20kill%20four%20more%20men%2C%20bringing%20his%20total%20number%20of%20murder%20victims%20to%2017%2C%20the%20Times%20reported.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20July%20of%20that%20year%2C%20Tracy%20Edwards%2C%20a%2032-year-old%20African%20American%20man%2C%20was%20seen%20walking%20the%20streets%20with%20his%20hands%20handcuffed.%20He%20brought%20police%20officers%20to%20Dahmer's%20house%2C%20which%20is%20where%20he%20said%20he%20was%20cuffed.%20When%20the%20officers%20entered%20the%20house%2C%20they%20saw%20photographs%20of%20body%20parts%20lying%20around.%20Dahmer%20was%20arrested%20on%20the%20spot.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDahmer%20was%20found%20guilty%20and%20sentenced%20to%2015%20consecutive%20life%20terms.%20He%20was%20killed%20in%20prison%20by%20a%20fellow%20inmate%20in%201994.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDahmer%20remains%20one%20of%20the%20nation's%20most%20disturbing%20serial%20killers.%20The%20chilling%20case%20became%20the%20subject%20of%20a%202017%20movie%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmy-friend-dahmer-ross-lynch-plays-jeffrey-dahmer-serial-killer-2017-11%5C%22%3E%26quot%3BMy%20Friend%20Dahmer%2C%26quot%3B%3C%2Fa%3E%20based%20on%20a%20graphic%20novel%2C%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fnetflix-jeffrey-dahmer-series-controversy-tiktok-romanticized-crimes-lgbtq-2022-10%5C%22%3Ethe%202022%20Netflix%20miniseries%3C%2Fa%3E%20%26quot%3BDahmer%20%E2%80%94%20Monster%3A%20The%20Jeffrey%20Dahmer%20Story.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3EPablo%20Escobar%2C%20the%20Colombian%20drug%20lord%2C%20was%20shot%20in%201993%20when%20he%20was%20on%20the%20run%20from%20authorities.%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%22590%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Pablo%20Escobar%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F5e67feb3235c180747351f74%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22442%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EPablo%20Escobar.%3Cp%3EAP%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EPablo%20Escobar%20became%20one%20of%20the%20richest%20people%20in%20the%20world%20in%20the%20late%20'80s%20and%20early%20'90s%20thanks%20to%20the%20cocaine%20trade%20that%20he%20controlled%20out%20of%20Colombia.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHis%20Medell%C3%ADn%20Cartel%20was%20responsible%20for%2080%25%20of%20the%20cocaine%20sent%20to%20the%20US%2C%20leaving%20thousands%20dead%2C%20per%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.wsj.com%2Fad%2Fcocainenomics%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EThe%20Wall%20Street%20Journal%3C%2Fa%3E.%20He%20became%20a%20target%20for%20the%20US%20and%20authorities%20in%20Colombia%2C%20so%20he%20went%20on%20the%20run.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOn%20December%202%2C%201993%2C%20Escobar%20attempted%20to%20escape%20the%20authorities%20by%20running%20across%20rooftops%20in%20Medellin%2C%20but%20he%20was%20killed%20in%20a%20shoot-out.%20His%20death%20marked%20the%20end%20of%20the%20country's%20reign%20on%20cocaine.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3EWhen%20Nicole%20Brown%20Simpson%20and%20Ron%20Goldman%20were%20found%20dead%20in%201994%2C%20O.J.%20Simpson%20was%20arrested%2C%20sparking%20the%20trial%20of%20the%20century.%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221786%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22oj%20simpson%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F5e680587235c18396b18b186%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221340%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EO.J.%20Simpson%20at%20his%20trial.%3Cp%3EAP%20Photo%2FSam%20Mircovich%2FPool%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EOn%20June%