aption%3EGary%20Ray%20Bowles.%3Cp%3EFlorida%20Department%20of%20Corrections%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EGary%20Ray%20Bowles%20killed%20his%20first%20victim%2C%20John%20Hardy%20Roberts%2C%20in%20Daytona%20Beach%20in%201994.%20From%20there%2C%20he%20murdered%20five%20more%20gay%20men%20along%20Interstate%2095%20in%20Maryland%2C%20Georgia%2C%20Atlanta%2C%20and%20Florida.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAt%20one%20of%20his%20crime%20scenes%2C%20Bowles%20left%20a%20probation%20document%2C%20and%20he%20was%20caught%20on%20surveillance%20camera%20taking%20money%20out%20of%20the%20victim's%20account.%20When%20he%20was%20finally%20caught%2C%20he%20was%20convicted%20of%20three%20out%20of%20the%20six%20murders.%20He%20was%20executed%20by%20lethal%20injection%20in%202019.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3EWhile%20at%20the%20height%20of%20her%20career%2C%20Latin%20singer%20Selena%20was%20killed%20in%20March%201995.%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221668%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22selena%20quintanilla%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F5e67eeac235c180255733494%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221251%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ESelena.%3Cp%3EBarbara%20Laing%20%2F%20Contributor%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20month%20before%20her%20murder%2C%20Selena%20Quintanilla%20(known%20mononymously%20as%20Selena)%20was%20at%20the%20height%20of%20her%20career%2C%20performing%20for%2060%2C000%20people%20at%20the%20Houston%20Astrodome.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHer%20album%20%26quot%3BAmor%20Prohibido%26quot%3B%20was%20nominated%20at%20the%20Grammys%20for%20best%20Mexican-American%20performance.%20She%20was%20also%20working%20on%20an%20English%20album%20that%20she%20hoped%20would%20transform%20her%20into%20a%20crossover%20hit.%20By%20all%20accounts%2C%20she%20was%20poised%20to%20become%20the%20next%20Gloria%20Estefan.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20everything%20changed%20in%20March%201995.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20year%20prior%2C%20she%20made%20Yolanda%20Sald%C3%ADvar%20the%20manager%20of%20the%20Selena%20fan%20club%20and%20put%20her%20in%20charge%20of%20the%20singer's%C2%A0boutiques.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESelena%20quickly%20noticed%20that%20there%20were%20money%20discrepancies%20and%20missing%20documents%20with%20both%20those%20businesses.%20Over%20the%20course%20of%20a%20couple%20of%20months%2C%20Selena%20confronted%20Sald%C3%ADvar%20about%20the%20missing%20documents.%20Ultimately%2C%20those%20conversations%20ended%20with%20Sald%C3%ADvar%20shooting%20Selena%20after%20they%20met%20at%20a%20hotel%20room%2C%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nytimes.com%2F1995%2F10%2F27%2Fus%2Fwoman-who-murdered-singer-gets-a-sentence-of-life-in-prison.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EThe%20New%20York%20Times%20reported%3C%2Fa%3E.%20She%20was%2023%20years%20old.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESald%C3%ADvar%20was%20convicted%20and%20sentenced%20to%20life%20in%20prison%20with%20no%20possibility%20of%20parole%20for%2030%20years.%20Meanwhile%2C%20Selena's%20song%20%26quot%3BDreaming%20of%20You%26quot%3B%20debuted%20after%20her%20death%20and%20reached%20the%20No.%201%20spot%20on%20the%20US%20Billboard%20200%20charts.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3EIn%201995%2C%20Timothy%20McVeigh%20parked%20a%20truck%20filled%20with%20explosives%20in%20front%20of%20a%20federal%20building%20in%20Oklahoma%20City%2C%20killing%20168%20people.%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221835%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22oklahoma%20city%20bombings%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F5e67d7ad235c181604166605%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221376%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EOklahoma%20City%20bombing.%3Cp%3EAP%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EOn%20April%2019%2C%201995%2C%20Timothy%20McVeigh%20rented%20a%20Ryder%20truck%20with%20agricultural%20fertilizer%2C%20diesel%20fuel%2C%20and%20other%20chemicals%20inside.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20parked%20the%20truck%20outside%20the%20Alfred%20P.%20Murrah%20Federal%20Building%20in%20Oklahoma%20City%20and%20walked%20to%20a%20getaway%20car.%20When%20the%20bomb%20went%20off%2C%20it%20destroyed%20the%20building%20and%20killed%20168%20people.%20Among%20them%2C%2019%20were%20children%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.cnn.com%2F2013%2F09%2F18%2Fus%2Foklahoma-city-bombing-fast-facts%2Findex.html%5C%22%3ECNN%3C%2Fa%3E%20reported.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20the%20FBI%20found%20a%20rear%20axle%20from%20the%20truck%20in%20the%20rubble%2C%20they%20quickly%20traced%20the%20piece%20back%20to%20McVeigh%2C%20a%20former%20US%20Army.%20From%20there%2C%20the%20evidence%20continued%20to%20build%20against%20McVeigh%3A%20He%20had%20traces%20of%20chemicals%20on%20his%20clothing%2C%20and%20he%20even%20jotted%20down%20notes%20about%20the%20bombing%20beforehand.%20The%20FBI%20also%20found%20that%20two%20other%20men%20knew%20about%20the%20bombing%20plot%20and%20helped%20him%20devise%20the%20plan.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMcVeigh%20was%20convicted%20on%2015%20counts%20of%20murder%20and%20was%20sentenced%20to%20death.%20He%20was%20executed%20in%202001.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3EA%20bomb%20went%20off%20at%20the%20Summer%20Olympic%20Games%20in%20Atlanta%20in%201996%2C%20leading%20to%20the%20deaths%20of%20two%20people.%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221720%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22atlanta%20olympics%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F5e67f395235c1802fe36e5b2%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221290%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%20Atlanta%20Centennial%20Olympic%20Park.%3Cp%3EMichael%20Green%2F%20AP%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EOn%20July%2027%2C%201996%2C%20police%20received%20an%20anonymous%20phone%20call%20telling%20them%20a%20bomb%20would%20go%20off%20in%2030%20minutes%20at%20the%20Centennial%20Olympic%20Park%20in%20Atlanta.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20the%20location%20was%20being%20evacuated%2C%20the%20bomb%20went%20off%20early.%20A%20woman%20was%20killed%2C%20and%20a%20cameraman%20who%20was%20rushing%20to%20the%20scene%20also%20suffered%20a%20fatal%20heart%20attack%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.cnn.com%2F2013%2F09%2F18%2Fus%2Folympic-park-bombing-fast-facts%2Findex.html%5C%22%3ECNN%3C%2Fa%3E%20reported.%20More%20than%20100%20more%20were%20injured.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAt%20first%2C%20security%20guard%20Richard%20Jewell%2C%20who%20found%20the%20backpack%20that%20held%20the%20bomb%2C%20was%20identified%20as%20a%20suspect.%20Eventually%2C%20Jewell%20was%20cleared%20of%20any%20wrongdoing.%20This%20series%20of%20events%20was%20covered%20in%20the%202019%20film%20%26quot%3BRichard%20Jewell.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20crime%20went%20unsolved%20until%201998%2C%20when%20a%20series%20of%20bombings%20in%20the%20South%20linked%20Eric%20Robert%20Rudolph%20to%20the%20Olympic%20bombings.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20eluded%20police%20for%20several%20more%20years%20and%20was%20eventually%20arrested%20in%202003.%20Rudolph%20was%20convicted%20and%20was%20sentenced%20to%20four%20consecutive%20life%20sentences.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3EOn%20September%2013%2C%201996%2C%20Tupac%20Shakur%20was%20killed%20in%20a%20drive-by%20shooting%20in%20Las%20Vegas.%20His%20rival%2C%20the%20Notorious%20BIG%2C%20was%20murdered%20in%20a%20similar%20way%20six%20months%20later.%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221845%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Tupac%20Shakur%20in%201994%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F5e7136d7235c18156e0a8816%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221384%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ETupac%20Shakur%20pictured%20in%201994.%3Cp%3ERon%20Galella%2FRon%20Galella%20Collection%20via%20Getty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3ETupac%20Shakur%20made%20a%20name%20for%20himself%20as%20an%20acclaimed%20rapper%20whose%20music%20fought%20against%20injustice%20toward%20Black%20Americans.%20Shakur%20made%20hit%20after%20hit%2C%20creating%20four%20platinum%20albums%20throughout%20his%20career.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20o